John Fashanu and TBoss were some of the popular faces that attended the premiere of a new Nollywood film, ‘Adini,’ in Abuja. The premiere was held at the Silverbird Cinema, Abuja with several personalities in attendance. Also in attendance were the film’s executive producer, Prophet I O Samuel, Rita Edochie, Browny Igboegwu, Gulder Ultimate Search star, Dennis Okike, Black Solo, Alaberry, Samirah Fashina, Ralph Okechukwu and others.   Deba Uwadiae to release ‘Imela’     Adebizz is face of Topklass     J. Jeff releases different gospel package   The Gabriel Jah Concept film, created using live-action 3D and compositing techniques tells the story of how a girl gets hypnotized by her grandfather’s music, sees the futuristic version of herself in a trance and sets out on a journey to become her true self. - Advertisement - In a brief chat with Prophet Samuel, he said “Adini is a story of Humanity told from the African perspective of music, Art and Culture like you have never heard or seen it before. Adini is the first African Film to use Animation, live Action, Compositing and Virtual Production Combined as its production techniques and approach.”